## Patch: add missing-`packs` regression test

```powershell
Describe "CaveatRegistry Priority 0 regressions" {
    BeforeAll {
        . "$PSScriptRoot/../module/LLMWorkflow/retrieval/CaveatRegistry.ps1"
    }

    It "Does not throw when a custom caveat omits triggers.packs" {
        $registry = @{
            caveats = @{
                'custom-caveat-no-packs' = @{
                    caveatId = 'custom-caveat-no-packs'
                    category = 'common-misconception'
                    subject = 'Custom caveat without packs'
                    message = 'Test caveat'
                    triggers = @{
                        keywords = @('custom keyword')
                    }
                    severity = 'warning'
                }
            }
            usageStats = @{
                totalTriggers = 0
                lastTriggerAt = $null
            }
        }

        $script:CaveatRegistryInstance = $registry

        { Find-ApplicableCaveats -Query 'custom keyword appears here' } | Should -Not -Throw

        $matches = Find-ApplicableCaveats -Query 'custom keyword appears here'
        $matches.Count | Should -Be 1
        $matches[0].Caveat.caveatId | Should -Be 'custom-caveat-no-packs'
    }
}
```

Expected effect:
- fails against implementations that assume `triggers.packs` always exists
- passes once `Find-ApplicableCaveats` guards missing `packs` safely
